<META NAME="description" Content="Consumers Water Company (CWC) is a water resource management company that has operating subsidiaries in Illinois, Ohio, Pennsylvania, New Jersey, New Hampshire, and Maine. CWC currently provides water and wastewater services to 222,865 residential, commercial and industrial
customers and provides professional and engineering services to utilities, industry, governmental entities, and other engineering firms across the country.
CAT specializes in water conservation, corrosion control, metering, distribution system evaluation, contract
operations, and environmental engineering.Consumers Water Company currently owns eight water utilities with 27 separate systems. Our customer base is
66% residential, 13% commercial, 8% industrial and 13% other.">

<META NAME="keywords" Content="water utility, wastewater, water resource, water resource management, water quality, water systems, water engineering and technical services, investor-owned water systems, drinking water, contract operations, corrosion control, metering, distribution system evaluation, contract operations, environmental engineering">

